One of your friends happens to be able to get you a job.
It has nothing to do with what you studied and it doesn't pay the same as your Junior role.
Despite this, you spend your days with your friend, surrounded by people, happy.
[background arg="res://Assets/Images/ending_clear.PNG" fade="0.0"]
Eventually, the company you worked at—and countless others run by Thinking Machines—fail, and the economy enters a recession.
In the evenings, your art consistently improves over days, weeks, months, and years.
[signal arg="game_end"]